raw_data.title: Network Engineer I
raw_data.description: Installs, configures and maintains the information transport (backbone) and Wide Area Network (WAN). Installs and maintains routers, switches, and assorted hubs. Provides proactive and reactive management of resources by monitoring and controlling the transport and associated components. Maintains network systems including backups. Modifies switch, router, and hub configurations to ensure optimum network performance and appropriate security processes. Manages and controls Internet and Remote dial-in network access. Has an understanding of Secure Dial-Up Point-to-Point Protocol. Responds to detected security incidents, network faults, and user reported outages at the time of the help desk referral.

raw_data.title: IT Technician I
raw_data.description: This position performs electronic assembly, mechanical assembly, installations, and repair of electronic and digital circuits and equipment. Must be able to properly operate test equipment and reach schematic/wire diagrams. Must be able to perform electronic and mechanical test in accordance with written test procedures.

raw_data.title: IT Technician II
raw_data.description: This position is responsible for operation and use of electronic test equipment; reading and interpreting schematic diagrams, wire lists and drawings, and use and operation of PC-based computer systems, networks, and terminals

raw_data.title: Technical Support/Training Specialist
raw_data.description: Investigates and resolves computer software and hardware problems of users. Receives telephone calls from users with problems, using knowledge of computer hardware, software and procedures to assist in diagnosing cause. Schedules and/or performs on-site assistance when required.

labor_categories.labor_category: Senior Electronic Systems Technician (Electronic Technician/ Maintenance II

raw_data.title: Senior Electronic Systems Technician (Electronic Technician/ Maintenance II
raw_data.description: Tests, troubleshoots, repairs and modifies developmental and production electronic equipment and systems. Analyses and interprets test data. Diagnoses cause of electrical or mechanical malfunction and performs corrective or preventive maintenance. Recommends changes in circuitry or installation to simplify assembly or maintenance. Instructs and supervises other technical personnel.

raw_data.title: Information Assurance Technology Technician I
raw_data.description: PC and client/server support responsible for diagnosing, troubleshooting and resolving client issues with hardware or software maintenance, installations, and upgrades; provides service by communicating with technical and non-technical staff; resolves computer problems in person, via telephone or from a remote location; provides assistance concerning the use of computer hardware and software, including printing, installation, word processing, electronic mail, applications, accounts, services, and operating systems.
